#: Game.Levels.FinsuppWorld.L07_FinsuppAddition
msgid "You proved that §0 distributes over addition of §1s.\n"
"\n"
"## The additivity pattern\n"
"\n"
"When working with §2 on sums, the pattern is:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Split**: §3 decomposes §4 into\n"
"   §5, given two mild conditions on §6.\n"
"2. **Evaluate**: §7 evaluates each piece when the\n"
"   summands are §8s.\n"
"\n"
"## Side conditions\n"
"\n"
"Both conditions on §9 are natural:\n"
"- §10: the function does nothing on zero values.\n"
"- §11: the function is additive in\n"
"  the value argument.\n"
"\n"
"For §12, both hold by §13 because the identity function\n"
"is additive and sends §14 to §15.\n"
"\n"
"## Algebraic perspective\n"
"\n"
"The fact that §16 distributes over addition means it is an\n"
"additive homomorphism. This is the formal backbone of constructions\n"
"like polynomial evaluation: evaluating §17 at a point is the\n"
"same as evaluating §18 and §19 separately and adding.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"Summing over a sum of finitely supported\n"
"functions equals summing each one separately and adding the results.\""
msgstr ""

