#: Game.Levels.BinomialCoefficients.L04_PascalsRule
msgid "The proof is a single rewrite — Pascal's rule is exactly this identity!\n"
"\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"With §1: §2.\n"
"\n"
"## Why Pascal's rule matters\n"
"\n"
"Pascal's rule is the *definition* of §3 in Lean (along with\n"
"the boundary conditions). Every other identity about binomial coefficients\n"
"is ultimately proved by induction using this recursion.\n"
"\n"
"## Combinatorial meaning\n"
"\n"
"Consider a set §4 with §5 elements. Fix one element §6.\n"
"The §7-element subsets of §8 split into two disjoint groups:\n"
"- Those that *include* §9: choosing the remaining §10 elements from\n"
"  the other §11 elements gives §12 subsets.\n"
"- Those that *exclude* §13: choosing all §14 elements from the\n"
"  other §15 elements gives §16 subsets.\n"
"\n"
"Adding these gives Pascal's rule.\n"
"\n"
"## What comes next\n"
"\n"
"The next level uses Pascal's rule *in action* to compute specific\n"
"values by hand."
msgstr ""

