#: Game.Levels.CountingPigeonhole.L08_ApplyingPigeonhole
msgid "You used §0 to extract an actual\n"
"collision from the pigeonhole principle.\n"
"\n"
"## Two forms of pigeonhole\n"
"\n"
"| Form | Statement | Use case |\n"
"|------|-----------|----------|\n"
"| Non-injectivity | §1 | When you only need to know injectivity fails |\n"
"| Collision | §2 | When you need the actual colliding pair |\n"
"\n"
"The collision form is stronger: from §3 you can\n"
"derive §4, but not vice versa (without further work).\n"
"\n"
"## The API choice\n"
"\n"
"Notice the input: §5 (strict inequality,\n"
"codomain < domain). This is equivalent to the non-injectivity condition\n"
"but is stated as a cardinality comparison that you prove with §6 and\n"
"arithmetic.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"Among 5 objects placed in 4 slots, at least two\n"
"objects share a slot.\""
msgstr ""

