#: Game.Levels.ListBasics.L10_Practice
msgid "You proved that membership in an append is symmetric: if an element\n"
"is in §0, it is also in §1.\n"
"\n"
"This level introduced two important new skills:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Rewriting hypotheses**: §2 transforms a hypothesis\n"
"   instead of the goal. This is the backward counterpart of the §3\n"
"   you already know. Any §4 that works on the goal can also be\n"
"   applied to a hypothesis using §5.\n"
"\n"
"2. **Case-splitting on disjunctions**: §6 splits\n"
"   a hypothesis §7 into two subgoals -- one where §8,\n"
"   and one where §9. You name the new hypotheses yourself.\n"
"\n"
"Together, these let you **analyze** membership hypotheses, not just\n"
"**construct** membership goals. You can now reason in both directions.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"If §10 appears somewhere in the concatenation\n"
"§11, then it must be in either §12 or §13 -- and either\n"
"way, it appears in §14.\""
msgstr ""

