#: Game.Levels.ListUnderLenses.L02_MultisetPerspective
msgid "# The multiset lens\n"
"\n"
"Now let us look at §0 through the **multiset** lens.\n"
"\n"
"Recall from the Multisets and Hierarchy world:\n"
"- A multiset forgets **order** but keeps **multiplicity**.\n"
"- Convert a list to a multiset using the coercion §1.\n"
"- §2 counts elements (with multiplicity).\n"
"- §3 converts multiset membership back to list membership.\n"
"\n"
"## What changes?\n"
"\n"
"When we coerce §4 to a multiset:\n"
"- The **order** is forgotten. We can no longer say \"the first element is 1.\"\n"
"- The **multiplicity** is preserved: §5 still appears twice, and §6 and §7\n"
"  each appear once.\n"
"- The **cardinality** is still 4 (same as the list length).\n"
"\n"
"## What stays the same?\n"
"\n"
"- Membership: §8 still holds.\n"
"- Cardinality: §9.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove two facts about §10 viewed as a multiset:\n"
"1. Its multiset cardinality equals the original list length.\n"
"2. The element §11 is a member of the multiset.\n"
"\n"
"For cardinality, you will find that §12 is\n"
"true **by definition** -- the coercion preserves the count. For membership,\n"
"you will need the **reduce-then-compute** pattern from the Multisets world."
msgstr ""

