msgid "# Composing Permutations\n"
"\n"
"Permutations can be **composed**: if §0 and §1 are permutations,\n"
"then §2 is the permutation that first applies §3,\n"
"then applies §4.\n"
"\n"
"## Multiplication in §5\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §6 has a group structure. The multiplication\n"
"§7 composes the two permutations:\n"
"\n"
"§8\n"
"\n"
"**Warning**: the order is reversed! §9 means \"first apply §10,\n"
"then apply §11.\" This matches the convention in algebra where\n"
"§12.\n"
"\n"
"After rewriting with §13, use §14 to evaluate:\n"
"\n"
"§15\n"
"\n"
"So §16, which you compute by first evaluating §17,\n"
"then evaluating §18 at the result.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Compose the swaps §19 and §20 on §21, and evaluate\n"
"the composition at §22.\n"
"\n"
"The computation: §23 first applies §24 to §25.\n"
"Since §26 and §27, the swap §28 fixes §29. Then we\n"
"apply §30 to §31, getting §32.\n"
"\n"
"So §33."
