#: Game.Levels.ListUnderLenses.L03_FinsetPerspective
msgid "# The finset lens\n"
"\n"
"Now the third lens: **finsets**. A finset forgets both order **and**\n"
"multiplicity, keeping only the **distinct** elements.\n"
"\n"
"Recall from the Multisets and Hierarchy world:\n"
"- §0 converts a multiset to a finset by removing duplicates.\n"
"- §1 counts the number of **distinct** elements.\n"
"\n"
"## What changes this time?\n"
"\n"
"When we convert the multiset §2 to a finset:\n"
"- The duplicate §3 is removed.\n"
"- The resulting finset is §4.\n"
"- The cardinality drops from 4 to **3**.\n"
"\n"
"This is the crucial difference: **the finset has fewer elements** than\n"
"the list or multiset, because the repeated §5 is counted only once.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove two facts about §6 viewed through the finset lens:\n"
"1. Converting to a finset gives §7.\n"
"2. The finset has cardinality 3.\n"
"\n"
"Both are concrete computations that §8 can handle."
msgstr ""

