#: Game.Levels.PermutationWorld.L01_PermDef
msgid "# Permutations of Finite Types\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to the world of **permutations**!\n"
"\n"
"## The idea\n"
"\n"
"A **permutation** of a set is a bijection from the set to itself — a\n"
"rearrangement of its elements. If you have a set §0, a\n"
"permutation might send §1, §2, §3.\n"
"\n"
"The set of all permutations of an §4-element set forms a group called\n"
"the **symmetric group** §5, with §6 elements.\n"
"\n"
"## §7 in Mathlib\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, a permutation of a type §8 is an element of §9,\n"
"which is defined as §10 — the type of equivalences (bijections)\n"
"from §11 to itself.\n"
"\n"
"Since §12 is just §13, a permutation §14\n"
"can be applied to any §15 to get §16.\n"
"\n"
"## Swaps\n"
"\n"
"The simplest nontrivial permutation is a **swap** (or transposition):\n"
"it exchanges two elements and fixes everything else.\n"
"\n"
"Mathlib provides §17, which swaps §18 and §19.\n"
"The key evaluation rules are:\n"
"\n"
"§20\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that swapping §21 and §22 in §23 sends §24 to §25."
msgstr ""

