#: Game.Levels.FinsuppWorld.L01_WhatIsFinsupp
msgid "# Finitely Supported Functions\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to the world of **finitely supported functions**!\n"
"\n"
"## The idea\n"
"\n"
"In many areas of mathematics, you work with functions that are nonzero\n"
"at only finitely many points. Examples include:\n"
"\n"
"- **Polynomials**: A polynomial §0\n"
"  is a function from §1 to a ring, where §2 for only\n"
"  finitely many §3.\n"
"- **Free abelian groups**: An element of the free abelian group on a set\n"
"  §4 is a function §5 that is nonzero at finitely many\n"
"  points.\n"
"- **Formal sums**: A finite formal sum §6 is\n"
"  a function §7 with finite support.\n"
"\n"
"## §8 in Mathlib\n"
"\n"
"Mathlib captures this idea with the type §9, pronounced\n"
"\"finitely supported functions from §10 to §11.\" Here §12 must have\n"
"a zero element (an instance of §13), and §14 consists of\n"
"functions §15 such that §16 for only finitely many §17.\n"
"\n"
"The notation §18 is syntactic sugar for §19.\n"
"\n"
"## Evaluating a §20\n"
"\n"
"A §21 can be applied to any element of §22 — it is a *total*\n"
"function, not a partial function. If §23, then §24\n"
"is defined for every §25.\n"
"\n"
"The simplest §26 is §27, which sends §28 to §29\n"
"and everything else to §30. The evaluation rule is:\n"
"\n"
"§31\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Evaluate §32 at the point §33. The result should be §34.\n"
"\n"
"Use §35 to unfold the definition, then\n"
"§36 to resolve the conditional (since §37 is true)."
msgstr ""

