#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L08_FunctionOnFin
msgid "# Computing with Functions on §0\n"
"\n"
"A powerful use of §1 is verifying properties of specific\n"
"functions defined on §2. Instead of proving a proposition about all\n"
"elements, you **check what the function does on each input**.\n"
"\n"
"## Functions on §3 by cases\n"
"\n"
"Consider a function §4 defined as §5.\n"
"\n"
"To verify that §6 sends every element to a value below §7, we:\n"
"1. §8 to pick an arbitrary input\n"
"2. §9 to enumerate all three inputs\n"
"3. Verify the output for each: §10, §11, §12 --- all §13\n"
"\n"
"This is the **function verification by exhaustion** pattern. It is the\n"
"computational sibling of the universal-property proofs from earlier levels,\n"
"but the framing is different: we think of the proof as \"checking the\n"
"function's output table.\"\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Define §14 by §15. Prove that the\n"
"sum of §16's outputs equals §17.\n"
"\n"
