msgid "# Using the inductive hypothesis\n"
"\n"
"In the previous level, you did not need the inductive hypothesis §0.\n"
"This time you will.\n"
"\n"
"## The key insight\n"
"\n"
"In finset induction, the inductive step gives you:\n"
"- §1 — the element being inserted\n"
"- §2 — the smaller finset\n"
"- §3 — non-membership proof\n"
"- §4 — the inductive hypothesis: the property holds for §5\n"
"\n"
"When the property involves cardinality, you typically:\n"
"1. Use §6 to rewrite §7\n"
"   as §8.\n"
"2. Use §9 to handle the §10 part.\n"
"3. Close the arithmetic with §11.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §12 by finset induction.\n"
"\n"
"- **Base case**: §13 — trivially §14.\n"
"- **Inductive step**: §15.\n"
"  Use §16 to rewrite the card, getting §17.\n"
"  This is a contradiction (a natural number plus 1 is never 0)."
msgstr ""

