#: Game.Levels.PascalsTriangle.L01_RowZero
msgid "# Pascal's Triangle, Row by Row\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to **Pascal's triangle**! In the Binomial Coefficients world,\n"
"you learned the recursive definition of §0 and the key\n"
"lemmas. Now we will build Pascal's triangle *row by row*, computing\n"
"each entry and seeing how the patterns emerge from the recursion.\n"
"\n"
"## Pascal's triangle\n"
"\n"
"§1\n"
"\n"
"Each row §2 contains the values §3.\n"
"\n"
"## Row 0\n"
"\n"
"Row 0 of Pascal's triangle consists of a single entry: §4.\n"
"\n"
"Since choosing 0 elements from 0 elements can be done in exactly one\n"
"way (take the empty set), we have §5.\n"
"\n"
"The row is simply: **[1]**.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §6."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `Fin 2`
