#: Game.Levels.FinsetTransformations.L03_Image
msgid "# §0: applying a function to every element\n"
"\n"
"While §1 selects elements, §2 **transforms** them.\n"
"Given a function §3 and a finset §4, the\n"
"expression §5 is the finset of all outputs of §6 on\n"
"elements of §7.\n"
"\n"
"The key membership lemma is:\n"
"\n"
"§8\n"
"\n"
"An element §9 belongs to the image exactly when there is **some**\n"
"element §10 with §11. This is an **existential**: you need\n"
"a witness.\n"
"\n"
"## Important difference from §12\n"
"\n"
"- §13 produces a **conjunction** (§14): membership and predicate.\n"
"- §15 produces an **existential** (§16): a witness and a proof.\n"
"\n"
"These are fundamentally different proof obligations.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §17 belongs to the image of {1, 2, 3} under the doubling\n"
"function §18.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**: Rewrite with §19, then provide the\n"
"witness §20 (since §21)."
msgstr ""

