#. §5: `↑ : List α → Multiset α`
#: Game.Levels.MultisetHierarchy.L04_InformationLossLists
msgid "You have now **experienced** information loss, not just been told about it.\n"
"\n"
"The two lists §0 and §1 are genuinely different: they have\n"
"different first elements, different orderings. Yet when you coerce them to\n"
"multisets with §2, the difference vanishes. The multiset §3\n"
"and the multiset §4 are the **same object**.\n"
"\n"
"This is what it means for the coercion §5 to\n"
"\"forget order\": it is a many-to-one function. Multiple distinct inputs\n"
"(different orderings of the same elements) map to a single output.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"Two different sequences can fill the same bag.\n"
"Once the items are in the bag, you cannot tell which sequence put them there.\""
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.BigOpAdvanced.L02_SumFilterSplit
