#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L02_SemicolonCombinator
msgid "The §0 combination is a workhorse pattern for §1\n"
"arithmetic. It works whenever:\n"
"- §2 is a specific number (not a variable),\n"
"- the property involves arithmetic that §3 can verify.\n"
"\n"
"Note how this is different from the W1 boss approach, where we used\n"
"§4 and then §5. That approach works for *any* §6,\n"
"because §7 can reason about the inequality §8 abstractly.\n"
"The §9 approach works only for *specific* small §10, but it is\n"
"more powerful: it can verify properties that don't follow from §11\n"
"alone.\n"
"\n"
"**Remember**: §12 is not specific to §13 or §14. It is a\n"
"general tactic combinator that applies the right-hand tactic to every\n"
"goal the left-hand tactic creates. Think of it as \"do this to all\n"
