#: Game.Levels.ListBasics.L09_Nodup
msgid "# Lists with no repeated elements\n"
"\n"
"The property §0 asserts that every element of §1 appears\n"
"exactly once -- the list has **no duplicates**.\n"
"\n"
"For example:\n"
"- §2 is true (all elements are distinct)\n"
"- §3 is false (§4 appears twice)\n"
"\n"
"## Why this matters\n"
"\n"
"The distinction between lists with and without duplicates is at the heart\n"
"of the **List → Multiset → Finset** hierarchy that structures this course:\n"
"\n"
"- A **list** has order and may have duplicates: §5\n"
"- A **multiset** forgets order but keeps duplicates: §6\n"
"- A **finset** forgets order and removes duplicates: §7\n"
"\n"
"§8 is the exact condition under which a list can be converted\n"
"to a finset **without losing information about which elements are present**.\n"
"\n"
"## The key lemma\n"
"\n"
"For concrete lists, §9 is the workhorse:\n"
"§10\n"
"\n"
"A cons-list has no duplicates if and only if the head does not appear in\n"
"the tail **and** the tail itself has no duplicates.\n"
"\n"
"## The §11 tactic\n"
"\n"
"After unfolding §12, you will encounter goals like §13.\n"
"These non-membership goals involve checking a concrete value against\n"
"each element of a concrete list -- a tedious but mechanical task.\n"
"\n"
"The §14 tactic can close such goals automatically. It applies a\n"
"library of pre-proved simplification lemmas to reduce the goal until\n"
"it is solved. Think of §15 as a calculator for \"obvious\" facts\n"
"about concrete data.\n"
"\n"
"We introduce §16 here specifically for these concrete membership\n"
"checks. You will see §17 used in much greater depth in later courses.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove two things:\n"
"1. The list §18 has no duplicates\n"
"2. The element §19 **is** in the list §20\n"
"\n"
"The second part demonstrates exactly what prevents §21 from\n"
"being §22: unfolding §23 on §24 would require\n"
"§25, but §26 -- so the proof would be blocked.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy for part 1**:\n"
"1. §27 to split the conjunction\n"
"2. §28 to unfold the outermost cons\n"
"3. §29 to split into non-membership and tail-Nodup\n"
"4. §30 to close the non-membership goal\n"
"5. Repeat for the inner cons cells\n"
"6. §31 for the base case\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy for part 2**:\n"
"Use §32 and §33/§34 to navigate membership,\n"
"finishing with §35."
msgstr ""

