#: Game.Levels.PermutationWorld.L06_ListPermVsEquivPerm
msgid "# Two Notions of \"Permutation\"\n"
"\n"
"The word **permutation** is used in two different ways in mathematics:\n"
"\n"
"1. **A rearrangement relationship**: \"The list §0 is a\n"
"   permutation of the list §1.\" This is a *statement*\n"
"   comparing two lists.\n"
"\n"
"2. **A bijection**: \"Let §2 be a permutation of §3.\"\n"
"   This is a *function* from the set to itself.\n"
"\n"
"Lean and Mathlib formalize these as two distinct concepts, and confusing\n"
"them is a common source of errors.\n"
"\n"
"## §4 — a relation on lists\n"
"\n"
"§5 (also written §6) is a **proposition**\n"
"asserting that §7 is a rearrangement of §8 — they contain the\n"
"same elements with the same multiplicities.\n"
"\n"
"It is built inductively. One key constructor is:\n"
"\n"
"§9\n"
"\n"
"This says: swapping the first two elements of a list produces a\n"
"permutation.\n"
"\n"
"## §10 — a type of bijections\n"
"\n"
"§11 is a **type** — the type of bijections from §12 to §13.\n"
"An element §14 is a *function* you can apply to elements.\n"
"\n"
"## The distinction\n"
"\n"
"| Concept | Type | Kind |\n"
"|---------|------|------|\n"
"| §15 | §16 | A *relation* between two lists |\n"
"| §17 | §18 | A *function type* (bijection §19) |\n"
"\n"
"They are fundamentally different: §20 compares two lists,\n"
"while §21 *is* a function.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that the list §22 is a permutation of §23\n"
"(as lists of §24), using §25."
msgstr ""

