#: Game.Levels.CountingPigeonhole.L04_NonemptyWitness
msgid "# From nonempty to witness\n"
"\n"
"Before we can state the pigeonhole principle, we need two proof moves\n"
"that connect cardinality to existence and emptiness. This level covers\n"
"the first: **extracting a witness from a nonempty finset**.\n"
"\n"
"## The move\n"
"\n"
"If you know §0 for a finset §1, this means §2.\n"
"In fact, §3 is *defined* as §4. So you can\n"
"destructure it with §5:\n"
"§6\n"
"This gives you a concrete element §7 and a proof §8.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Given a nonempty finset §9, produce an element of §10 and a proof that\n"
"it belongs to §11."
