msgid "You built a §0 nonzero at two points by adding two §1s,\n"
"then evaluated it.\n"
"\n"
"## The construction pattern\n"
"\n"
"To build a §2 nonzero at points §3 with values\n"
"§4, use:\n"
"§5\n"
"\n"
"To evaluate, use §6 to split, then §7 on each piece.\n"
"\n"
"## Why addition?\n"
"\n"
"Using addition to combine §8s is natural because §9 forms\n"
"an additive monoid (and an additive group when §10 is one). This means:\n"
"- §11 is the zero function (sending everything to §12).\n"
"- §13 adds pointwise.\n"
"- §14 is the \"basis element\" at §15 with coefficient §16.\n"
"\n"
"This additive structure is what makes §17 useful for representing\n"
"free modules, polynomial rings, and similar algebraic constructions.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"To build a function nonzero at several points,\n"
"add together §18s — one for each point.\""
