#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L03_Decide
msgid "# The §0 Tactic\n"
"\n"
"There is an even more powerful automation tactic for finite types: §1.\n"
"\n"
"The §2 tactic works on **decidable propositions** --- statements that\n"
"can be checked by a finite computation. Many propositions about §3\n"
"are decidable, because §4 is a finite type with decidable equality.\n"
"\n"
"When §5 works, it simply *computes* the answer. No case analysis,\n"
"no arithmetic reasoning --- just brute-force evaluation.\n"
"\n"
"## When does §6 work?\n"
"\n"
"§7 works when:\n"
"- The proposition involves only finite types and decidable operations\n"
"- The computation terminates in reasonable time\n"
"- The type checker can verify the result\n"
"\n"
"For small §8, this is almost always the case.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §9.\n"
"\n"
"This is a decidable proposition --- we can simply check whether §10 and §11\n"
"are equal in §12. They are not, so the proposition is true.\n"
"\n"
"Try just §13."
msgstr ""

