#: Game.Levels.MatrixWorld.L01_MatrixDef
msgid "# Matrices as Functions over Finite Types\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to the **Matrix** world!\n"
"\n"
"## The big idea\n"
"\n"
"In linear algebra, a matrix is a rectangular grid of numbers. In\n"
"Lean's Mathlib, a matrix is something even simpler: **a function of\n"
"two arguments**.\n"
"\n"
"The type §0 is *defined* as §1 — a function\n"
"from row indices §2 and column indices §3 to entries of type §4.\n"
"\n"
"So a §5 matrix of natural numbers has type\n"
"§6, which is literally §7.\n"
"\n"
"## Why this definition?\n"
"\n"
"This functional definition means:\n"
"- **Constructing** a matrix = defining a function\n"
"- **Accessing** an entry §8 = applying a function\n"
"- **Equality** of matrices = extensional equality of functions\n"
"\n"
"The finite-type infrastructure you built earlier (§9, §10,\n"
"§11, big operators) now becomes the backbone of matrix theory.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §12 is *definitionally* equal to\n"
"§13. Since §14 is defined as\n"
"§15, this is true by §16."
msgstr ""

