#: Game.Levels.FinsetTransformations.L01_Filter
msgid "# Filtering a finset by a predicate\n"
"\n"
"In the previous world you learned to combine finsets using union,\n"
"intersection, and difference. Now we turn to **transformations** that\n"
"build new finsets from old ones by testing or modifying elements.\n"
"\n"
"## §0\n"
"\n"
"Given a finset §1 and a predicate §2, the expression\n"
"§3 (or equivalently §4) returns the\n"
"finset of elements of §5 that satisfy §6.\n"
"\n"
"The key membership lemma is:\n"
"\n"
"§7\n"
"\n"
"An element belongs to the filtered finset exactly when it belongs to\n"
"the original finset **and** satisfies the predicate.\n"
"\n"
"## §8\n"
"\n"
"Filtering requires a §9 instance -- Lean must be able\n"
"to compute §10 for each element. For predicates built from numeric\n"
"comparisons, §11, §12, etc., Lean can infer this\n"
"automatically.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §13 belongs to the finset obtained by filtering\n"
"{1, 2, 3, 4, 5} with the predicate \"is even\" (i.e., §14).\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**: Rewrite with §15 to split the goal into\n"
"a conjunction, then prove each part."
msgstr ""

