#: Game.Levels.FinThreeExamples.L07_InjectivityFails
msgid "# A Specific Function from §0 to §1 Is Not Injective\n"
"\n"
"In the previous level, you saw that a function from §2 to §3\n"
"cannot be surjective (not enough inputs to cover all outputs). The dual\n"
"statement is: a function from §4 to §5 cannot be injective\n"
"(too many inputs for too few outputs --- two inputs must collide).\n"
"\n"
"This is the other face of the **pigeonhole principle**: if you put 4\n"
"pigeons into 3 holes, at least two pigeons share a hole.\n"
"\n"
"## The function\n"
"\n"
"Consider the function §6 defined by:\n"
"- §7\n"
"- §8\n"
"- §9\n"
"- §10\n"
"\n"
"Notice that §11, but §12 in §13. So §14 is not\n"
"injective.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove §15. After §16 (assuming injectivity\n"
"for contradiction), apply §17 to the collision: since §18\n"
"(both equal §19), injectivity would force §20 in §21.\n"
"\n"
"Write §22. Here §23\n"
"proves §24 because the function sends both to §25.\n"
"\n"
"Then derive a contradiction from §26: use\n"
"§27 to get §28 at the natural number\n"
"level, and §29 to close."
msgstr ""

