msgid "You proved two things:\n"
"1. §0 -- every element appears exactly once\n"
"2. §1 -- the number §2 is in the list §3\n"
"\n"
"The second fact reveals **why** the list §4 fails §5.\n"
"When you unfold §6 on §7, the first condition\n"
"requires §8. But you just proved §9, so that\n"
"condition is false. The §10 proof is blocked at the very first step.\n"
"\n"
"**Key concepts**:\n"
"- §11 is defined recursively: each head must be fresh (not in\n"
"  the tail), and the tail must itself have no duplicates\n"
"- §12 unfolds one layer: §13\n"
"- §14 is the base case: §15\n"
"- §16 closes \"obvious\" goals about concrete data, such as §17\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: A list has no duplicates when every element appears\n"
"at most once. To verify this, check each element against those that follow.\n"
"If any element reappears later, §18 fails.\n"
"\n"
