msgid "There are exactly 81 functions from §0 to §1.\n"
"\n"
"## The paper explanation\n"
"\n"
"> *A function §2 is determined\n"
"> by four independent choices: §3, §4, §5, and §6.\n"
"> Each choice has 3 options. By the multiplication principle, the\n"
"> total number of functions is §7.*\n"
"\n"
"The exponential formula §8 captures\n"
"this: the codomain size is the **base** (each input chooses from\n"
"§9 options) and the domain size is the **exponent** (there are\n"
"§10 independent choices).\n"
"\n"
"## Comparing previous computations\n"
"\n"
"| Function type | Count | Formula |\n"
"|---------------|-------|---------|\n"
"| §11 | 9 | §12 |\n"
"| §13 | 8 | §14 |\n"
"| §15 | 81 | §16 |\n"
"\n"
"The same principle, different numbers.\n"
"\n"
"**Transfer check**: You can now explain in ordinary language why the\n"
"number of functions from an §17-element set to an §18-element set\n"
"is §19."
msgstr ""

