#: Game.Levels.FinsetOperations.L05_IntroducingExt
msgid "# Proving finset equality with §0\n"
"\n"
"So far you have proved **membership** facts: showing that a specific\n"
"element belongs to a specific finset expression. But what about proving\n"
"that two finsets are **equal**?\n"
"\n"
"## The extensionality principle\n"
"\n"
"Two finsets are equal if and only if they have the same elements:\n"
"\n"
"§1\n"
"\n"
"This is the **extensionality** principle: the identity of a finset is\n"
"determined entirely by its members.\n"
"\n"
"## The §2 tactic\n"
"\n"
"The tactic §3 converts a goal §4 into §5,\n"
"then introduces §6 for you. After §7, you need to prove a\n"
"biconditional §8.\n"
"\n"
"To prove a biconditional §9, use §10 to split into two\n"
"implications §11 and §12, then prove each separately.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §13 for arbitrary finsets §14 and §15. This is\n"
"the **commutativity of union**.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**: Use §16 to reduce to membership, then §17\n"
"to split the biconditional. In each direction, rewrite with\n"
"§18 and use §19 to swap the disjuncts."
msgstr ""

