#: Game.Levels.FinsetConstructors.L01_EmptyFinset
msgid "The empty finset is the starting point for building all other finsets.\n"
"Every finset can be constructed by starting from §0 and adding elements\n"
"one at a time (using §1, which you will learn shortly).\n"
"\n"
"This is analogous to how every list can be built from §2 using §3,\n"
"and every natural number can be built from §4 using §5. The empty\n"
"finset is the **base case** of finset construction.\n"
"\n"
"**Notation**: In Lean, §6 and §7 both refer to §8. You\n"
"will see both in mathlib. We will use §9 when emphasizing emptiness\n"
"and §10 notation when listing specific elements.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"The empty set has no elements. In Lean, it is\n"
"written §11 or §12.\""
msgstr ""

