#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L07_ModularArithmetic
msgid "# Arithmetic on §0 Is Modular\n"
"\n"
"§1 is not just an index type --- it supports arithmetic operations.\n"
"But unlike natural number arithmetic, arithmetic on §2 **wraps around**\n"
"modulo §3.\n"
"\n"
"## Addition wraps\n"
"\n"
"In §4:\n"
"- §5 because §6\n"
"\n"
"## Subtraction wraps too (and this surprises people!)\n"
"\n"
"In §7:\n"
"- §8 because §9\n"
"\n"
"On natural numbers, §10 (truncated subtraction). But on §11,\n"
"subtraction wraps around: §12.\n"
"\n"
"## Multiplication wraps\n"
"\n"
"In §13:\n"
"- §14 because §15\n"
"\n"
"You might expect §16, but in §17, the result wraps to §18.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove the subtraction wrapping fact: §19.\n"
"\n"
"This is a concrete computation in §20. The §21 tactic can verify\n"
"it by evaluating both sides."
msgstr ""

