#: Game.Levels.Capstone.L04_PigeonholeProduct
msgid "# Pigeonhole meets cardinality\n"
"\n"
"The pigeonhole principle says: if the domain is larger than the\n"
"codomain, the function cannot be injective — there must be a collision.\n"
"\n"
"## The setup\n"
"\n"
"Consider a function §0.\n"
"\n"
"- The domain §1 has §2 elements (by §3).\n"
"- The codomain §4 has §5 elements (by §6).\n"
"- Since §7, pigeonhole guarantees a collision.\n"
"\n"
"## The proof plan\n"
"\n"
"1. **Apply pigeonhole**: §8 to reduce\n"
"   the problem to proving §9.\n"
"2. **Compute cardinalities**: §10 + §11 to get §12.\n"
"3. **Close arithmetic**: §13.\n"
"\n"
"This integrates counting from the **FintypeClass** / **CountingPigeonhole**\n"
"worlds with the product-type infrastructure from **FinCompute** / **FintypeClass**."
msgstr ""

