#: Game.Levels.BinomialTheorem.L08_AlternatingSum
msgid "## Why the alternating sum is zero\n"
"\n"
"**Algebraic proof** (from the binomial theorem):\n"
"\n"
"Set §0 in §1. For §2:\n"
"\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"Since §4 and §5... the\n"
"exact manipulation is a bit fiddly, but the key idea is clear:\n"
"substituting §6 makes alternating signs appear.\n"
"\n"
"**Combinatorial proof**:\n"
"\n"
"The even-sized subsets and odd-sized subsets of a nonempty set pair up.\n"
"For each element §7 in the set, the map §8\n"
"(symmetric difference with §9) is a bijection between even-sized\n"
"and odd-sized subsets. So §10,\n"
"which means the alternating sum is zero.\n"
"\n"
"## Transfer\n"
"\n"
"On paper: *\"Set §11 in the binomial theorem to get\n"
"§12 for §13.\"*\n"
"\n"
"## What comes next\n"
"\n"
"The next level is a **transfer** level: stating the binomial theorem\n"
"in ordinary mathematical notation."
msgstr ""

