#: Game.Levels.FinThreeExamples.L07_InjectivityFails
msgid "The function §0 from §1 to §2\n"
"is not injective because §3, yet §4 in §5.\n"
"\n"
"The proof by contradiction:\n"
"1. Assume §6\n"
"2. Since §7 (both equal §8), apply §9 to get §10 in §11\n"
"3. But §12 --- contradiction!\n"
"\n"
"**Dual of the surjectivity failure**: In Level 6, you showed that\n"
"§13 cannot be surjective (not enough inputs). Here you\n"
"showed that §14 cannot be injective (too many inputs).\n"
"These are two faces of the same coin --- the pigeonhole principle.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof move**: To disprove injectivity, find a *specific collision*:\n"
"two distinct inputs with the same output. Apply injectivity with §15\n"
"(where §16 witnesses §17), then derive a contradiction from\n"
"the resulting false equality.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"The function §18 with §19, §20,\n"
"§21 sends both §22 and §23 to §24. Since §25 but\n"
"§26, the function is not injective.\""
msgstr ""

