#: Game.Levels.BigOpAdvanced.L05_Conv
msgid "You used §0 to rewrite inside a big-operator binder!\n"
"\n"
"## Why §1 matters\n"
"\n"
"Many big-operator goals require normalizing the expression *inside*\n"
"the sum before you can apply lemmas like §2 or\n"
"§3. Without §4, you would need §5 with a\n"
"pointwise proof — which works, but is heavier. §6 gives you\n"
"a direct, surgical rewrite.\n"
"\n"
"## §7 vs. §8\n"
"\n"
"| Approach | When to use |\n"
"|----------|-------------|\n"
"| §9 | Quick, one-step rewrites inside a binder |\n"
"| §10 | When you need a more complex pointwise argument |\n"
"\n"
"Both achieve the same result. §11 is more convenient for simple\n"
"cases; §12 is more flexible when the pointwise proof requires\n"
"multiple steps.\n"
"\n"
"## Transfer\n"
"\n"
"The §13 tactic has no direct analogue in paper proofs. On paper,\n"
"you would simply say \"rewriting each term\" or \"since §14\n"
"for each §15.\" In Lean, §16 is the mechanism that makes this\n"
"possible.\n"
"\n"
"## What comes next\n"
"\n"
"The next level introduces another new tactic: §17, for monotone\n"
"inequality goals."
msgstr ""

