#: Game.Levels.FinsetExploration.L04_ImageUnderSquaring
msgid "# Squaring every element of {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}\n"
"\n"
"Recall §0 applies a function §1 to every element of §2\n"
"and collects the results (removing duplicates). The key lemma:\n"
"\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that the image of {1, 2, 3, 4, 5} under the squaring function\n"
"§4 is {1, 4, 9, 16, 25}.\n"
"\n"
"Since §5 is injective on {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}, no duplicates are\n"
"removed: the image has the same number of elements as the source.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**: Use §6 to reduce to membership, then §7 with\n"
"the image and insert membership lemmas, and handle each direction."
msgstr ""

