#: Game.Levels.BinomialTheorem.L09_Transfer
msgid "## The binomial theorem: a summary\n"
"\n"
"You have now seen the binomial theorem from multiple angles:\n"
"\n"
"| Level | What you did |\n"
"|-------|-------------|\n"
"| L01 | Applied §0 to a concrete numerical example |\n"
"| L03 | Applied §1 in §2 (general §3) |\n"
"| L04 | Specialized at §4 to derive the row sum |\n"
"| L09 | Stated the theorem over §5 as a transfer exercise |\n"
"\n"
"## Key identities derived from the binomial theorem\n"
"\n"
"| Substitution | Identity |\n"
"|-------------|---------|\n"
"| §6 | §7 |\n"
"| §8 | §9 for §10 |\n"
"\n"
"## Transfer: the inductive proof\n"
"\n"
"The proof of the binomial theorem proceeds by induction on §11:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Base case** (§12): §13, and the sum has one term\n"
"   §14. ✓\n"
"\n"
"2. **Inductive step**: Assume the theorem holds for §15. Then\n"
"   §16. Distribute, use the inductive\n"
"   hypothesis, and recombine using Pascal's rule\n"
"   §17.\n"
"\n"
"The formal proof in mathlib follows exactly this structure.\n"
"\n"
"## What comes next\n"
