#. §21: `sum_range_succ`
#. §22: `induction`
#. §23: `rw [sum_range_succ]`
#. §24: `rw [ih]`
#. §25: `ring`
#: Game.Levels.RangeSumInduction.L09_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing the **Range Sum Induction** world!\n"
"\n"
"You proved a non-trivial sum identity by induction, combining:\n"
"1. §0 to set up the proof structure\n"
"2. §1 for the base case\n"
"3. §2 to peel off the last term\n"
"4. The inductive hypothesis §3 to replace the inner sum\n"
"5. §4 to close the polynomial arithmetic\n"
"\n"
"## What you learned in this world\n"
"\n"
"- **L01**: §5 review — §6\n"
"- **L02**: §7 — the peeling-off lemma\n"
"- **L03**: First inductive sum — §8\n"
"- **L04**: The §9 tactic for step-by-step equalities\n"
"- **L05**: §10 — introducing §11 in the inductive step\n"
"- **L06**: Sum of odd numbers — §12\n"
"- **L07**: Explicit §13 walkthrough of the inductive step\n"
"- **L08**: Base case pitfalls — §14 and §15\n"
"- **L09**: Boss — integrating everything\n"
"\n"
"## Transfer moment\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary mathematics, you would write:\n"
"\n"
"> *We prove by induction on n.*\n"
">\n"
"> *Base case*: When §16, the sum is empty and equals §17.\n"
"> Also §18. ✓\n"
">\n"
"> *Inductive step*: Assume §19.\n"
"> Then §20. ✓\n"
"\n"
"This is exactly what §21 + §22 does in Lean.\n"
"The §23 step corresponds to \"peel off the last term\",\n"
"the §24 step corresponds to \"apply the inductive hypothesis\",\n"
"and §25 corresponds to \"verify the algebra\".\n"
"\n"
"## What comes next\n"
"\n"
"The next world will apply these techniques to a specific classic formula\n"
"in more depth."
msgstr ""

