#: Game.Levels.MultisetHierarchy.L11_CardinalityInequality
msgid "# From specific instance to general principle\n"
"\n"
"In Level 10, you saw that §0 has multiset cardinality 4 but\n"
"finset cardinality 3. The specific numbers (4 and 3) are not the point --\n"
"what matters is the **inequality**: the finset can never have **more**\n"
"elements than the multiset.\n"
"\n"
"## §1\n"
"\n"
"This general fact is a theorem in mathlib:\n"
"\n"
"§2\n"
"\n"
"The finset obtained by deduplication has at most as many elements as the\n"
"original multiset. Equality holds exactly when the multiset already has\n"
"no duplicates.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove this inequality for the specific multiset §3.\n"
"\n"
"Instead of computing both sides and comparing (which §4 could do),\n"
"use the general lemma §5. The\n"
"underscore §6 tells Lean to fill in the multiset argument automatically.\n"
"\n"
"This demonstrates the **derive-then-instantiate** pattern: a general\n"
"theorem (§7) gives you the specific instance for free."
msgstr ""

