#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L09_ModularMultiplication
msgid "You just proved two surprising facts about §0:\n"
"\n"
"1. §1: the product of two nonzero elements equals one of the factors.\n"
"2. §2: a nonzero element squared gives zero!\n"
"\n"
"Fact 2 is the most striking. In ordinary arithmetic, §3 implies\n"
"§4 or §5. In §6, the element §7 is a **zero divisor** ---\n"
"it is nonzero, but §8.\n"
"\n"
"This happens because §9 is not prime. In §10 for a prime §11,\n"
"there are no zero divisors --- every nonzero element has a\n"
"multiplicative inverse. This is why §12 is a\n"
"field, while §13 is only a ring.\n"
"\n"
"**Takeaway**: Arithmetic on §14 wraps modulo §15. When §16 is\n"
"composite, you get zero divisors. When §17 is prime, you get a field."
msgstr ""

