#: Game.Levels.FinIntro.L12_CongrArg
msgid "§0 is a fundamental tool: from §1, you can derive\n"
"§2 for *any* function §3. Here you used\n"
"§4 to extract a value-level equality from a §5-level\n"
"equality.\n"
"\n"
"This is the converse of what §6 does:\n"
"- §7 goes from \"values equal\" to \"Fin elements equal\"\n"
"- §8 goes from \"Fin elements equal\" to \"values equal\"\n"
"\n"
"You will use this pattern in the boss level: given a hypothesis that two\n"
"§9 elements are equal, §10 extracts the numerical\n"
"consequence, which you can then use for arithmetic reasoning with §11.\n"
"\n"
"**In paper proofs**: this step corresponds to \"If §12 as elements\n"
"of §13, then in particular their underlying values are equal.\"\n"
"This is so obvious on paper that mathematicians rarely state it explicitly --\n"
"but in Lean, §14 makes it formal."
msgstr ""

