#: Game.Levels.RangeSumInduction.L08_BaseCasePitfalls
msgid "# Base case: §0\n"
"\n"
"In every inductive sum proof so far, the base case was just §1.\n"
"That worked because Lean's kernel can see that §2\n"
"reduces to §3.\n"
"\n"
"But why does it reduce? Let us spell it out.\n"
"\n"
"## The base case, step by step\n"
"\n"
"The base case goal is always:\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"The key facts are:\n"
"- **§5**: §6\n"
"- **§7**: §8\n"
"\n"
"So you can always prove the base case by:\n"
"\n"
"§9\n"
"\n"
"Understanding this mechanism matters: if the right-hand side does not\n"
"reduce to §10 at §11, you may need §12 + §13\n"
"explicitly, followed by arithmetic.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that the sum over §14 is §15 for *any* function\n"
"§16.\n"
"\n"
"Use §17 to introduce the function, then rewrite with\n"
"§18 and §19."
msgstr ""

