#: Game.Levels.CountingFunctions.L05_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing the Counting Functions world!\n"
"\n"
"You proved that the number of functions §0 equals\n"
"§1: three choices for the first\n"
"input, times three choices for the second input.\n"
"\n"
"## The multiplication principle\n"
"\n"
"The exponential rule §2 is the\n"
"iterated multiplication principle: a function from §3 to §4 is\n"
"determined by §5 independent choices, each from §6\n"
"options. The total is a product of §7 copies of §8,\n"
"which is §9.\n"
"\n"
"## What you learned in this world\n"
"\n"
"| Concept | Level | Key item |\n"
"|---------|-------|----------|\n"
"| Counting all functions | L01 | §10 |\n"
"| Counting injective functions | L02 | §11 |\n"
"| No surjection from small to large | L03 | §12 |\n"
"| Functions to Bool as subsets | L04 | §13 |\n"
"| The multiplication principle | L05 | Integration |\n"
"\n"
"## Transfer moment\n"
"\n"
"In paper mathematics, you would write:\n"
"\n"
"> *There are §14 functions from a 2-element set to a 3-element set.\n"
"> Of these, §15 are injective and none are surjective.\n"
"> More generally, §16 by the\n"
"> multiplication principle: each of the §17 inputs independently\n"
"> chooses from §18 outputs.*\n"
"\n"
"The Lean proof mechanizes each step: §19 states the\n"
"exponential rule, §20 evaluates the specific sizes,\n"
"and arithmetic closes the computation. The mathematical insight is\n"
"identical."
