#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L11_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing the Computing with Fin world!\n"
"\n"
"Your boss proof combined three different skills:\n"
"1. **§0** to split a conjunction into parts\n"
"2. **§1** to evaluate a numeric equality with powers\n"
"3. **§2 + §3** to verify a power inequality for each element\n"
"\n"
"Notice how each part demanded a different approach:\n"
"- Part 1 was a pure numeric equality --- §4 evaluated it directly\n"
"- Part 2 needed §5 + §6 (exhaustive case analysis with\n"
"  per-case numeric evaluation)\n"
"\n"
"This is the core lesson: **choose the right tool for each subgoal**.\n"
"\n"
"## What you learned in this world\n"
"\n"
"| Tactic | What it does | When to use |\n"
"|--------|-------------|-------------|\n"
"| §7 | Splits §8 into §9 goals | Exhaustive verification on small §10 |\n"
"| §11 | Evaluates decidable propositions | Concrete equalities/inequalities on finite types |\n"
"| §12 | Evaluates numeric expressions | Powers, products, non-linear arithmetic |\n"
"| §13 | Applies a tactic to all goals | After §14, §15, etc. |\n"
"\n"
"**The exhaustive verification pattern:**\n"
"§16\n"
"This pattern checks a property for every element of a small finite type.\n"
"It is the Lean equivalent of \"we verify the claim for each element of\n"
"the domain\" in paper proofs.\n"
"\n"
"**The tactic selection hierarchy:**\n"
"| Situation | Strategy |\n"
"|-----------|----------|\n"
"| Concrete equality/inequality on small §17 | §18 (or §19) |\n"
"| Universal property needing per-case computation | §20 or §21 |\n"
"| Property following from the bound §22 alone | §23 + §24 |\n"
"\n"
"**Transfer to paper proofs**: The proof you just wrote says:\n"
"\"We prove two facts. First, §25 by direct\n"
"computation. Second, for each §26, we check\n"
"§27: the values are §28, all less than §29.\"\n"
"\n"
"In the next worlds, you will work with §30 as a concrete example\n"
"world, and then move beyond §31 to study lists, multisets, and\n"
"finsets --- the richer finite collections built on the §32 foundation."
msgstr ""

