#: Game.Levels.FinsetCardinality.L07_InclusionExclusion
msgid "# The inclusion-exclusion principle\n"
"\n"
"This is the central identity of cardinality theory for finite sets.\n"
"\n"
"## The principle\n"
"\n"
"When you take the union of two sets §0 and §1, elements in the overlap\n"
"§2 are counted once in §3 and once in §4, but only once in §5.\n"
"This gives the fundamental identity:\n"
"\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, this is:\n"
"\n"
"§7\n"
"\n"
"## The additive form\n"
"\n"
"Notice that Lean states this in **additive** form: both sides are sums.\n"
"In ordinary math, you often see the **subtractive** form:\n"
"\n"
"§8\n"
"\n"
"The additive form avoids subtraction on natural numbers (which can\n"
"underflow), so it is cleaner in Lean.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove the inclusion-exclusion identity for two specific finsets:\n"
"§9 and §10.\n"
"\n"
"Their union is §11 (4 elements) and their intersection is\n"
"§12 (2 elements). So §13. Verify this using the\n"
"general lemma."
msgstr ""

