#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L07_ModularArithmetic
msgid "In §0, subtraction wraps around: §1.\n"
"\n"
"This is **modular arithmetic** --- the same arithmetic you use when\n"
"reading a clock. On a 12-hour clock, 3 hours before 1 o'clock is\n"
"10 o'clock (wrapping past 0). In §2, the modulus is §3.\n"
"\n"
"Key facts about §4 arithmetic:\n"
"- Addition is defined as §5\n"
"- Subtraction wraps: §6\n"
"- Multiplication wraps: §7\n"
"- §8 with §9 forms a **commutative ring** with these operations\n"
"- The zero element is §10\n"
"\n"
"Notice that §11 handled this easily --- it just evaluated both\n"
"sides. For concrete equalities in §12, §13 is the right tool.\n"
"\n"
"**Why this matters**: Modular arithmetic on §14 connects finite\n"
"types to number theory. In later worlds, when you study permutations\n"
"or functions on §15, understanding this arithmetic structure will\n"
"be essential.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"Arithmetic in §16 is\n"
"performed modulo 5. Since §17,\n"
"we have §18 in this ring.\""
msgstr ""

