#: Game.Levels.FinsuppWorld.L03_FinsuppSupport
msgid "You computed the support of a §0.\n"
"\n"
"## The support concept\n"
"\n"
"The support is a §1 — not a §2 — which means it carries\n"
"concrete, computable data about which points are nonzero. This is the\n"
"key advantage of §3 over arbitrary functions: the finiteness of\n"
"the nonzero set is baked into the type.\n"
"\n"
"## Two views of support\n"
"\n"
"| Lemma | What it says |\n"
"|-------|-------------|\n"
"| §4 | §5 |\n"
"| §6 | §7 |\n"
"\n"
"The first is the general characterization. The second is the computation\n"
"rule for the §8 constructor.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"The support of a finitely supported function is\n"
"the finite set of points where it is nonzero. For §9, that\n"
"set is just §10 (provided §11).\""
msgstr ""

