#: Game.Levels.FinIntro.L07_Concretize
msgid "# Concretizing §0\n"
"\n"
"So far you have worked with the boundary cases §1 (empty) and §2\n"
"(singleton). Let's now look at a type with more than one element.\n"
"\n"
"§3 has exactly three elements: §4, §5, and §6. These are distinct --\n"
"no two of them are the same.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §7.\n"
"\n"
"The tactic §8 will introduce the hypothesis §9\n"
"and change the goal to §10. Then you need to derive a contradiction.\n"
"\n"
"One approach: §11 extracts §12 at the §13\n"
"level, then §14 spots the contradiction.\n"
"\n"
"A simpler approach: after §15, try §16.\n"
"The §17 tactic can decide the negation §18\n"
"directly.\n"
"\n"
"Or simplest of all: §19 can handle the entire goal in one step, since\n"
"inequality of §20 literals reduces to inequality of natural numbers."
msgstr ""

