#: Game.Levels.FinsetInduction.L09_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing the Finset Induction world!\n"
"\n"
"You proved §0: the cardinality of a union is at most the\n"
"sum of the individual cardinalities. This required:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Finset induction** on §1 (the new proof principle from this world)\n"
"2. **§2** to decompose the union at the insert boundary\n"
"3. **§3** to bound the cardinality increase (from L05)\n"
"4. **§4** with §5 (the non-membership\n"
"   hypothesis that makes finset induction work)\n"
"5. **The inductive hypothesis** §6 (combined via §7)\n"
"\n"
"## What you learned in this world\n"
"\n"
"| Level | Key lesson | Key lemma/move |\n"
"|-------|-----------|----------------|\n"
"| L01 | Nat induction review | §8 |\n"
"| L02 | Finset induction intro | §9 |\n"
"| L03 | Using §10 for contradiction | §11 at a hypothesis |\n"
"| L04 | Vacuous base case | §12 + §13 |\n"
"| L05 | §14 on membership | §15, §16 |\n"
"| L06 | Subset card inequality | §17 |\n"
"| L07 | Nat vs Finset induction | Choose by parameter type |\n"
"| L08 | §18 for induction | §19 |\n"
"| L09 | Integration | All of the above |\n"
"\n"
"## Transfer moment\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary mathematics, the proof of §20 is almost\n"
"trivial: every element of §21 is in §22 or §23 (or both), so\n"
"counting with multiplicity gives at most §24.\n"
"\n"
"The Lean proof is structurally different — it uses induction rather than\n"
"a counting argument — but the key insight is the same: insertion can\n"
"add at most one element, so the union cannot have more elements than\n"
"the combined count.\n"
"\n"
"## What comes next\n"
"\n"
"The next world is the **Finset Reasoning** problem set, where you\n"
"retrieve finset skills (membership, set operations, cardinality,\n"
"induction) under reduced scaffolding on fresh surface forms."
msgstr ""

