#: Game.Levels.PermutationWorld.L04_Identity
msgid "# The Identity Permutation\n"
"\n"
"Every group has an **identity element** — the element that does nothing.\n"
"For the symmetric group §0, the identity permutation fixes every\n"
"element: §1 for all §2.\n"
"\n"
"## §3 and §4\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, the identity permutation is written as §5.\n"
"Under the hood, it equals §6:\n"
"\n"
"§7\n"
"\n"
"The reflexivity equivalence §8 is the identity function on §9:\n"
"it sends every element to itself. After rewriting with §10, applying\n"
"the result to any §11 gives §12 by §13.\n"
"\n"
"## Self-inverse property\n"
"\n"
"The identity also arises from composing a swap with itself. Since a\n"
"swap just exchanges two elements, doing it twice returns everything to\n"
"its original position:\n"
"\n"
"§14\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that every element of §15 is fixed by the identity permutation."
msgstr ""

