"\n"
"The **trace** of a square matrix is the sum of its diagonal entries:\n"
"\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"In Mathlib, §1. This directly uses the\n"
"big-operator machinery you learned in the **FinsetSum** / **BigOpAdvanced**\n"
"worlds, applied to the matrix representation from **MatrixWorld**.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Compute the trace of the diagonal matrix with entries §2\n"
"(indexed by §3):\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"## Strategy\n"
"\n"
"1. §5 — reduces §6 to §7.\n"
"2. §8 — expands the sum over §9 into three terms.\n"
"3. §10 — evaluates the arithmetic."
