#: Game.Levels.PermutationWorld.L02_ConcreteSwap
msgid "You verified the complete behavior of the swap §0 on §1.\n"
"\n"
"## Swaps as permutations\n"
"\n"
"A swap §2 is fully determined by two elements. On a type\n"
"with §3 elements, it fixes all §4 other elements. The three\n"
"evaluation lemmas (§5, §6,\n"
"§7) let you compute the output for any input.\n"
"\n"
"## A fact from algebra\n"
"\n"
"Every permutation can be written as a product of transpositions. So\n"
"§8 is not just a simple example — it is a *generator* for the\n"
"entire symmetric group §9.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"To describe a swap completely, you just need to\n"
"say which two elements it exchanges. Everything else stays put.\""
msgstr ""

