#: Game.Levels.FinIntro.L13_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing the first world!\n"
"\n"
"You proved that §0 and §1 never collide -- they\n"
"partition §2 into two disjoint pieces. This structural\n"
"fact is the basis for induction on finite types: to define a function\n"
"on §3, handle the §4 cases and the §5 case\n"
"separately.\n"
"\n"
"## What you learned\n"
"\n"
"1. **§6** is the type of natural numbers less than §7\n"
"2. **§8** constructs elements; §9 is shorthand\n"
"3. **§10** (or §11) extracts the underlying natural number\n"
"4. **§12** provides the proof that the value is in bounds\n"
"5. **Subtype extensionality** -- two §13 elements are equal iff their values are\n"
"6. **§14** is empty; **§15** is a singleton\n"
"7. **§16** is the largest element of §17 with value §18\n"
"8. **§19** embeds §20 into §21 preserving the value\n"
"9. **§22** maps §23 into §24 by incrementing the value\n"
"10. **§25** extracts consequences from equalities by applying a function\n"
"\n"
"## Transfer to paper proofs\n"
"\n"
"The proof you just wrote says:\n"
"\n"
"\"Suppose §26. Then their values are equal:\n"
"§27. But §28 since §29. Contradiction.\"\n"
"\n"
"This is a standard proof by contradiction. The §30 step is\n"
"\"suppose for contradiction,\" §31 extracts the\n"
"value-level consequence, and §32 derives the contradiction from\n"
"the arithmetic. Each tactic step corresponds to a sentence in the\n"
"paper proof -- this is the structure you should internalize.\n"
"\n"
"## What's next\n"
"\n"
"In the next world, you will learn §33 and §34, which let you\n"
"verify properties of §35 by checking all cases explicitly. Later in\n"
"the course, you will see that sums over §36 are intimately\n"
"connected to §37 -- each element of §38 corresponds to an element\n"
"of §39."
msgstr ""

