#: Game.Levels.FinsetConstructors.L04_NotationDesugaring
msgid "The curly-brace notation §0 is convenient, but it is important\n"
"to know what it hides. When you see §1 in a goal state, you are\n"
"looking at §2.\n"
"\n"
"This matters because:\n"
"- **Lemmas about §3** apply to literal finsets. When you need to\n"
"  prove §4, you are proving §5,\n"
"  which §6 can handle.\n"
"- **Order in notation**: §7 inserts §8 first (outermost),\n"
"  then §9, then §10 (innermost). But finsets have no order, so\n"
"  §11.\n"
"\n"
"## A preview of what is coming\n"
"\n"
"In later worlds, you will use §12 to prove membership:\n"
"§13\n"
"This recursive peeling -- \"either §14 is the element just inserted,\n"
"or §15 was already in the smaller finset\" -- is the key proof move\n"
"for membership in literal finsets.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"Writing §16 means: start with nothing,\n"
"add 3, add 2, add 1. The result is a set, so the order does not matter.\""
