#: Game.Levels.CountingPigeonhole.L08_ApplyingPigeonhole
msgid "# From non-injectivity to collision\n"
"\n"
"The pigeonhole principle says a function cannot be injective. But in\n"
"practice, we often want to find the actual **collision**: two distinct\n"
"inputs that map to the same output.\n"
"\n"
"Mathlib provides a stronger form:\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"This says: if the codomain is strictly smaller than the domain, then\n"
"there exist two distinct elements that §1 maps to the same value.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Given any function §2, prove that two distinct inputs\n"
"collide.\n"
"\n"
"The approach:\n"
"1. Apply §3.\n"
"2. Prove the cardinality condition: §4."
msgstr ""

