#: Game.Levels.FinIntro.L05_FinZero
msgid "# The empty type §0\n"
"\n"
"What natural numbers are less than §1? None!\n"
"\n"
"This means §2 has **no elements at all**. It is an empty type.\n"
"\n"
"If someone gives you an element §3, they have given you something\n"
"that cannot exist. From a false premise, you can prove anything -- this is\n"
"the principle of **ex falso** (\"from falsehood, anything follows\").\n"
"\n"
"## The proof move\n"
"\n"
"Rather than memorizing a magic function, let's discover *why* §4 is\n"
"impossible. If §5, then §6 carries a proof §7 that\n"
"§8. But no natural number is less than §9!\n"
"\n"
"Here is the plan:\n"
"1. Extract the impossible fact with §10\n"
"2. The §11 tactic recognizes that §12 is a contradiction\n"
"   among natural numbers and closes the goal\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that if you have an element of §13, you can derive §14.\n"
"\n"
"**Misconception alert (C5)**: §15 is empty -- it has zero elements.\n"
"§16 has one element (namely §17). Don't confuse the index with the\n"
"number of elements!"
