#: Game.Levels.CountingPigeonhole.L06_StatingPigeonhole
msgid "You just proved your first pigeonhole result!\n"
"\n"
"The proof followed the classic pattern:\n"
"1. Assume injectivity.\n"
"2. Derive §0 from §1.\n"
"3. Evaluate the cardinalities.\n"
"4. Reach a contradiction (§2).\n"
"\n"
"## The key lemma\n"
"\n"
"§3 is the formal engine behind pigeonhole.\n"
"If §4 is injective, then §5 --- each element of §6\n"
"maps to a *distinct* element of §7, so there must be at least as many\n"
"elements in §8.\n"
"\n"
"The contrapositive gives pigeonhole: if §9, then §10 cannot\n"
"be injective.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"If you have 4 items and only 3 boxes, at least\n"
"two items must share a box.\""
msgstr ""

