#: Game.Levels.ListUnderLenses.L04_ReorderingInvariance
msgid "# Permutation invariance\n"
"\n"
"In Level 1, we saw that §0 is a list with a specific order:\n"
"1 comes first, then 2, then 1 again, then 3.\n"
"\n"
"But as a multiset, the order is irrelevant. The list §1 --\n"
"which is the same elements in a different arrangement -- produces the\n"
"**same multiset**. And since both lists produce the same multiset, they\n"
"also produce the **same finset**.\n"
"\n"
"## §2\n"
"\n"
"Recall from the Multisets and Hierarchy world:\n"
"\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"Two coerced lists give equal multisets if and only if one is a\n"
"rearrangement (permutation) of the other.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove two facts:\n"
"1. §4 and §5 are the same multiset.\n"
"2. §6 and §7 are the same finset.\n"
"\n"
"For the multiset equality, use §8 to reduce to a\n"
"permutation check, then §9. This is the **reduce-then-compute** pattern.\n"
"\n"
"For the finset equality, §10 can directly verify it, since both\n"
"sides evaluate to the same concrete finset §11."
msgstr ""

