#: Game.Levels.FinsetConstructors.L06_DecidableEq
msgid "# The hidden requirement: §0\n"
"\n"
"Every finset operation you have used so far -- §1, §2,\n"
"membership testing -- works on §3. But could you build a\n"
"§4 of *any* type? Not quite.\n"
"\n"
"## The problem\n"
"\n"
"A §5 is a multiset with no duplicates. To check whether an\n"
"element is already present (so that §6 can avoid duplicates),\n"
"Lean needs to be able to **decide equality** on §7. This is the\n"
"type class §8.\n"
"\n"
"## What happens without §9\n"
"\n"
"Consider a type with no §10 instance:\n"
"\n"
"§11\n"
"\n"
"If you tried to write §12, Lean would produce\n"
"an error:\n"
"\n"
"§13\n"
"\n"
"Lean refuses to build the finset because it cannot check for duplicates.\n"
"The fix is §14 in the type definition:\n"
"\n"
"§15\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Below we define §16 with §17. Prove that\n"
"§18 equals §19\n"
"as finsets.\n"
"\n"
"This is a definitional equality (both sides desugar to\n"
"§20), so §21 works.\n"
"The key point: **this only compiles because §22 has §23**.\n"
"Without it, even writing §24 would fail."
