#: Game.Levels.FinsetOperations.L01_UnionMembership
msgid "# Finset union: combining two finsets\n"
"\n"
"You have learned to construct finsets, check membership, and use §0\n"
"to automate membership proofs. Now we begin studying **operations** on\n"
"finsets: ways to build new finsets from old ones.\n"
"\n"
"## The union operation\n"
"\n"
"Given finsets §1 and §2, their **union** §3 contains every element\n"
"that belongs to at least one of them. The key membership lemma is:\n"
"\n"
"§4\n"
"\n"
"This is the finset analogue of the set-theory fact: an element belongs\n"
"to a union if and only if it belongs to at least one of the two sets.\n"
"\n"
"## Notation\n"
"\n"
"The symbol §5 is typed §6 or §7. You will also see\n"
"§8 (intersection) and §9s = {1, 2, 3}§10t = {3, 4, 5}§112 ∈ s ∪ t§12Finset.mem_union§132 ∈ s§14simp`."
msgstr ""

