#: Game.Levels.FinsetCardinality.L08_CardFilterLe
msgid "You proved that filtering cannot increase cardinality. The lemma\n"
"§0 handles this in full generality — it works\n"
"for any predicate and any finset.\n"
"\n"
"## Intuition\n"
"\n"
"Filtering selects a subset. A subset cannot have more elements than\n"
"the original set. This is the cardinality analogue of §1:\n"
"\n"
"- §2 (subset relation)\n"
"- §3 (cardinality consequence)\n"
"\n"
"The inequality is a consequence of the subset relation, but\n"
"§4 is stated directly for convenience.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"Selecting elements that satisfy a property\n"
"from a set cannot produce more elements than the original set.\""
