#: Game.Levels.CountingPigeonhole.L01_SumCardinality
msgid "# Counting and Pigeonhole\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to the counting world! In the previous world you learned to compute\n"
"§0 for §1, §2, and product types. Now we extend this\n"
"to more type constructors, building toward the **pigeonhole principle**.\n"
"\n"
"## Sum types\n"
"\n"
"Given types §3 and §4, the **sum type** §5 contains every element\n"
"of §6 (wrapped as §7) and every element of §8 (wrapped as\n"
"§9). The cardinality of a sum is the sum of the cardinalities:\n"
"§10\n"
"\n"
"This is the formal version of the **addition principle**: if set §11 has\n"
"§12 elements and set §13 has §14 elements, and §15 and §16 are disjoint,\n"
"then §17 has §18 elements.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §19 has exactly 5 elements.\n"
"\n"
"Use §20 to split the sum, then §21 to\n"
