#: Game.Levels.PermutationWorld.L07_Boss
msgid "Congratulations on completing the **Permutations of Finite Types** world!\n"
"\n"
"You proved that every element of §0 satisfies §1, combining:\n"
"- **Counting** (§2 + §3 + factorial computation)\n"
"- **Group theory** (§4 — Lagrange's theorem)\n"
"\n"
"## What you learned in this world\n"
"\n"
"| Concept | Level | Key item |\n"
"|---------|-------|----------|\n"
"| Permutation definition (§5) | L01 | §6 |\n"
"| Concrete swap evaluation | L02 | §7 |\n"
"| Composition of permutations | L03 | §8, §9 |\n"
"| Identity permutation | L04 | §10 |\n"
"| Counting permutations | L05 | §11 |\n"
"| §12 vs §13 | L06 | §14 |\n"
"| Group-theoretic property | L07 | §15 |\n"
"\n"
"## Transfer moment\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary mathematics, you would say: \"By Lagrange's theorem, every\n"
"element of a finite group §16 satisfies §17. Since §18,\n"
"every permutation §19 satisfies §20.\"\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, this argument splits into two pieces:\n"
"1. A **counting** computation: §21 + §22\n"
"   to establish §23.\n"
"2. A **group theory** lemma: §24 for the abstract result.\n"
"\n"
"The connection between counting (factorial) and algebra (group order)\n"
"is exactly the bridge this world was designed to build.\n"
"\n"
"## What comes next\n"
"\n"
"The next worlds explore matrices as functions over finite types, and\n"
"further applications where permutations, finite types, and algebraic\n"
"structure interact."
msgstr ""

