#: Game.Levels.MultisetHierarchy.L12_NodupConnection
msgid "You connected two worlds:\n"
"\n"
"**Part 1** showed that §0 and §1 are the same\n"
"condition, just expressed at different levels of the hierarchy. If a list\n"
"has no duplicates, then its multiset also has no duplicates (and vice versa).\n"
"This is because §2 only cares about *which elements appear how many\n"
"times*, not about their *order* -- and order is the only thing forgotten\n"
"by the coercion.\n"
"\n"
"**Part 2** revealed the internal mechanism of §3:\n"
"1. §4 removes duplicates from the multiset, producing a §5 multiset\n"
"2. §6 bundles this §7 multiset into a §8\n"
"3. §9 extracts the underlying multiset from the §10\n"
"\n"
"So §11 -- the finset's underlying data is the\n"
"deduplicated multiset.\n"
"\n"
"**The full hierarchy in Lean types**:\n"
"§12\n"
"\n"
"- Step 1 forgets order (quotienting by permutations)\n"
"- Step 2 forgets multiplicity (deduplicating, then bundling with §13)\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"To get a set from a bag, remove the duplicates.\n"
"The result is a bag where every item appears exactly once -- which is\n"
"exactly what a set is.\""
msgstr ""

