#: Game.Levels.MultisetHierarchy.L07_CountSymbolic
msgid "You just proved a counting result **symbolically**: instead of letting §0\n"
"evaluate the entire expression at once, you first used §1 to\n"
"extract the structural fact (\"adding 1 increases the count of 1 by 1\"), then\n"
"computed the remaining piece.\n"
"\n"
"This is the difference between **computational** and **symbolic** reasoning:\n"
"- **Computational**: §2 evaluates the whole expression. Works for concrete\n"
"  data but gives no insight.\n"
"- **Symbolic**: §3 reveals the structure. Works for\n"
"  general arguments and teaches transferable reasoning.\n"
"\n"
"The two count lemmas form a recursive recipe:\n"
"- §4: counting §5 when the head is §6 → add 1\n"
"- §7: counting §8 when the head is not §9 → unchanged\n"
"\n"
"Together, they describe how §10 processes a multiset element by element --\n"
"just like §11 describes how membership processes a list.\n"
"\n"
"**Why did §12 work at the end?** After §13, the goal\n"
"became §14. Lean can compute §15\n"
"definitionally, reducing the goal to §16, which is also definitional.\n"
"So §17 (or even §18) closes it. The symbolic step was the rewrite;\n"
"the final computation is just cleanup.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"To count how many red marbles are in a bag, look at\n"
