#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L02_SemicolonCombinator
msgid "# The §0 Combinator\n"
"\n"
"Writing §1 three times (or four, or five) after §2 gets\n"
"tedious. Lean provides a shorthand: the **semicolon combinator** §3.\n"
"\n"
"## How §4 works\n"
"\n"
"§5 means: \"run §6, then apply §7\n"
"to **every** goal that §8 produced.\"\n"
"\n"
"So §9 means:\n"
"1. §10 --- split into one goal per element\n"
"2. §11 --- try to close each goal\n"
"\n"
"If §12 succeeds on every case, the whole proof is done in one line.\n"
"\n"
"**The §13 combinator is general.** It works with any pair of tactics,\n"
"not just §14 and §15. You will see patterns like\n"
"§16 or §17 in later worlds.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that for every §18, the value §19.\n"
