#: Game.Levels.FinsuppWorld.L06_FinsuppSum
msgid "You computed a sum over a §0 using §1.\n"
"\n"
"## Why the side condition?\n"
"\n"
"The lemma §2 requires §3. This ensures that\n"
"if the value at §4 were §5, the sum would be §6 — matching the\n"
"convention that §7 (the zero §8).\n"
"\n"
"In practice, this condition is almost always trivially satisfied:\n"
"- §9 satisfies it because §10.\n"
"- §11 satisfies it because §12.\n"
"- §13 satisfies it because §14.\n"
"\n"
"## Connection to big operators\n"
"\n"
"§15 is Mathlib's way of summing over a finitely supported\n"
"function without having to explicitly name the support as a §16.\n"
"It is used heavily in the definitions of polynomial evaluation,\n"
"free modules, and formal power series.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"Summing over a §17 means summing over\n"
"its support. For a §18, there is only one term.\""
