#: Game.Levels.FinThreeExamples.L05_Surjectivity
msgid "# Proving Surjectivity by Finding Preimages\n"
"\n"
"A function §0 is **surjective** if every element of the\n"
"codomain is hit: for every §1, there exists §2 with §3.\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §4 unfolds to §5.\n"
"\n"
"## The function\n"
"\n"
"Consider the same cyclic shift from the previous level:\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"Is this function surjective onto §7? Yes! Every element of §8\n"
"is hit:\n"
"- §9 is hit by §10\n"
"- §11 is hit by §12\n"
"- §13 is hit by §14\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that the cyclic shift is surjective. After §15, use\n"
"§16 to split into three cases --- one for each element of the\n"
"codomain. In each case, provide the preimage using §17.\n"
"\n"
"The §18 closes the equality because the function is defined by\n"
"pattern matching, so §19 computes to the target value."
msgstr ""

