msgid "# Why does §0 need §1?\n"
"\n"
"Look at the type of §2:\n"
"\n"
"§3\n"
"\n"
"where §4 must be an §5. Why?\n"
"\n"
"## The reason: order independence\n"
"\n"
"A §6 has **no order**. When you write §7,\n"
"there is no canonical order in which to add the terms. The sum could\n"
"be computed as:\n"
"- §8, or\n"
"- §9, or\n"
"- §10, etc.\n"
"\n"
"For the sum to be well-defined, all these orders must give the same\n"
"result. This is exactly what **commutativity** (§11) and\n"
"**associativity** (§12) guarantee.\n"
"\n"
"The **monoid** part provides a §13 element, which is needed for the\n"
"empty sum.\n"
"\n"
"Together, §14 ensures:\n"
"1. §15 exists (for §16)\n"
"2. §17 is associative (for regrouping)\n"
"3. §18 is commutative (for reordering)\n"
"\n"
