#: Game.Levels.BinomialTheorem.L06_VandermondeGeneral
msgid "# Vandermonde's Identity (Convolution)\n"
"\n"
"Vandermonde's identity is one of the great identities in combinatorics:\n"
"\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"It says that the number of ways to choose §1 elements from a set of\n"
"§2 elements equals the total over all ways to split the selection:\n"
"choose §3 from the first §4 elements and §5 from the last §6.\n"
"\n"
"## In Lean\n"
"\n"
"The mathlib lemma §7 states this using §8:\n"
"\n"
"§9\n"
"\n"
"Here §10 is the set of all pairs §11 with\n"
"§12. So §13 plays the role of §14 and `ij.2 = k - j$.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Apply Vandermonde's identity in general form."
msgstr ""

