#. §15: `decide`
#: Game.Levels.MultisetHierarchy.L03_PermAndEquality
msgid "# When are two multisets equal?\n"
"\n"
"Two multisets are equal when they contain the same elements with the same\n"
"multiplicities -- regardless of order. In Lean, this is captured by the\n"
"fact that §0 is a quotient by §1:\n"
"\n"
"If §2 (the lists are permutations of each other), then\n"
"§3.\n"
"\n"
"## §4\n"
"\n"
"§5 asserts that §6 can be rearranged into §7.\n"
"For concrete lists with decidable equality, §8 can verify this.\n"
"\n"
"## §9\n"
"\n"
"The key lemma is §10:\n"
"\n"
"§11\n"
"\n"
"This lets you convert between multiset equality and list permutation.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that the lists §12 and §13 give the same multiset.\n"
"\n"
"**Strategy**: Use §14 to reduce multiset equality\n"
"to a list permutation, then §15 to verify the permutation."
msgstr ""

