#. ```
#. §18: `Fin n`
#. §19: `by omega`
#: Game.Levels.PermutationWorld.L02_ConcreteSwap
msgid "# A Concrete Permutation\n"
"\n"
"In the previous level you saw that §0 sends §1 to §2.\n"
"Now you will verify all three outputs of the swap §3 on §4,\n"
"proving it is a complete description of a permutation.\n"
"\n"
"## The three cases\n"
"\n"
"For §5:\n"
"\n"
"| Input | Output | Why |\n"
"|-------|--------|-----|\n"
"| §6 | §7 | §8 |\n"
"| §9 | §10 | §11 |\n"
"| §12 | §13 | §14 (since §15 and §16) |\n"
"\n"
"## The third rule\n"
"\n"
"When the argument is *neither* of the swapped elements, use:\n"
"\n"
"§17\n"
"\n"
"You need to supply two proofs of inequality. For concrete §18 values,\n"
"§19 can close these.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove all three evaluation facts as a conjunction."
msgstr ""

