#: Game.Levels.RangeSumInduction.L08_BaseCasePitfalls
msgid "You proved that §0 for any function §1.\n"
"\n"
"## Why this matters\n"
"\n"
"The base case of any inductive sum proof is always trivial: the sum\n"
"over an empty range is §2. The two lemmas that make this work are:\n"
"\n"
"- §3\n"
"- §4\n"
"\n"
"In practice, §5 usually closes the base case automatically. But\n"
"knowing the mechanism helps when:\n"
"- You need to debug a proof that is not closing.\n"
"- The right-hand side at §6 does not reduce to §7 by itself.\n"
"- You want to write a transparent §8 proof.\n"
"\n"
"## Ready for the boss\n"
"\n"
"You now have all the tools:\n"
"- §9 to set up the proof\n"
"- §10 or §11 for the base case\n"
"- §12 for the inductive step\n"
"- §13 or §14 to close the arithmetic\n"
"- §15 for explicit step-by-step reasoning\n"
"\n"
"The boss will test them all."
msgstr ""

