#: Game.Levels.CountingFunctions.L04_BoolFunctions
msgid "There are exactly 8 functions from §0 to §1, corresponding\n"
"to the §2 subsets of a 3-element set.\n"
"\n"
"The proof was:\n"
"1. §3 gave: §4.\n"
"2. §5 and §6 evaluated: §7.\n"
"3. §8 computed: §9.\n"
"\n"
"## Functions to Bool as subsets\n"
"\n"
"This connection between §10 and subsets of §11 is fundamental:\n"
"- Each function §12 defines the subset\n"
"  §13.\n"
"- Each subset §14 defines the characteristic function\n"
"  §15.\n"
"\n"
"The number of subsets of an §16-element set is §17. This is why\n"
"the power set is denoted §18 or §19.\n"
"\n"
"## Comparing the two exponentials\n"
"\n"
"| Function type | Count | Formula |\n"
"|---------------|-------|---------|\n"
"| §20 | 9 | §21 (Level 1) |\n"
"| §22 | 8 | §23 (this level) |\n"
"\n"
"The codomain size is always the **base** of the exponential. The\n"
"domain size is always the **exponent**.\n"
"\n"
"**In plain language**: \"There are §24 binary strings of length 3,\n"
"or equivalently, §25 subsets of a 3-element set.\""
msgstr ""

