#: Game.Levels.FinCompute.L09_ModularMultiplication
msgid "# More Modular Arithmetic: Multiplication and Zero Divisors\n"
"\n"
"In the earlier level, you saw subtraction wrapping in §0. Now\n"
"let's see multiplication wrapping --- and a genuinely surprising consequence.\n"
"\n"
"In §1:\n"
"- You might expect §2, but §3, so\n"
"  §4.\n"
"\n"
"Even more strikingly:\n"
"- §5, because §6.\n"
"\n"
"This means §7 is a **zero divisor** in §8: a nonzero element whose\n"
"product with another nonzero element is zero. This cannot happen in\n"
"ordinary arithmetic, where §9 implies §10 or §11.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove both facts as a conjunction:\n"
"1. §12 (multiplication wraps)\n"
"2. §13 (zero divisor!)\n"
"\n"
"Use §14 to split, then §15 for each part."
