#: Game.Levels.FinsetCardinality.L01_CardEmpty
msgid "# Cardinality: counting elements systematically\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to the **Cardinality** world. You have already seen §0\n"
"in passing — you used §1 and §2 to\n"
"compute the size of literal finsets. Now we study cardinality as a\n"
"systematic topic.\n"
"\n"
"## The key question\n"
"\n"
"Given a finset §3, what is §4? This world answers that question\n"
"for progressively more complex finsets, culminating in the\n"
"**inclusion-exclusion principle**.\n"
"\n"
"## §5\n"
"\n"
"The simplest cardinality fact is:\n"
"\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"The empty finset has zero elements. This is the base case for all\n"
"cardinality reasoning — analogous to how §7 is the base case for\n"
"finset construction.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove that §8 using §9."
msgstr ""

#. §0: $n^{\\underline{n}} = n!$
#. §1: $n$
#. §2: $n$
#. §3: $n^{\\underline{n}} = n(n-1)\\cdots 2 \\cdot 1 = n!$
#. §4: $n+1$
#. §5: $n$
#. §6: ```
#. Nat.succ_descFactorial_succ (n k : ℕ) :
#.   (n + 1).descFactorial (k + 1) = (n + 1) * n.descFactorial k
#. ```
#. §7: $(n+1)^{\\underline{k+1}} = (n+1) \\cdot n^{\\underline{k}}$
#. §8: `Nat.descFactorial_succ`
#. §9: ```
#. n.descFactorial (k + 1) = (n - k) * n.descFactorial k
#. ```
#. §10: `succ_descFactorial_succ`
#. §11: `n.descFactorial n = Nat.factorial n`
#. §12: `n`
#: Game.Levels.Factorials.L05_DescFactorialSelf
msgid "# The key identity: §0\n"
"\n"
"When the descending factorial descends all the way — taking\n"
"all §1 terms from §2 — you get the ordinary factorial.\n"
"Intuitively: §3.\n"
"\n"
"## The helper lemma\n"
"\n"
"To prove this by induction, you will need a new lemma that\n"
"relates the descending factorial of §4 to that of §5:\n"
"\n"
"§6\n"
"\n"
"This says: §7.\n"
"\n"
"Compare this with §8, which uses subtraction:\n"
"\n"
"§9\n"
"\n"
"The §10 version avoids subtraction entirely,\n"
"which makes induction proofs cleaner.\n"
"\n"
"## Your task\n"
"\n"
"Prove §11 by induction on §12."
msgstr ""

